The paper deals with algorithms for the order-preserving matching problem, which involves searching for substrings in a text that have the same relative order as a given pattern. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithms, which suggests that it may be relevant to the categories of algorithms and complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
